[TextBlock(text='Here are the musical terms that best match your descriptions:

1. Homophony (or homophonic texture) - a single melodic line with harmonic accompaniment

2. Concerto Grosso - a Baroque form contrasting a small group of soloists (concertino) with full orchestra (ripieno)

3. Recapitulation - the third main section of sonata form where themes return in the tonic key

4. Sequence - a melodic or harmonic pattern repeated at different pitch levels

5. Classical Period - the era from approximately 1750-1825, following the Baroque and preceding the Romantic period